What is the purpose of the `prunespentwallettransactions` command in Verus?

The `prunespentwallettransactions` command is used to remove all spent transactions from your wallet, leaving only unspent transactions. You can also specify a transaction ID to keep, which will preserve that transaction and remove all others.

prunespentwallettransactions "txid"

Remove all txs that are spent. You can clear all txs bar one, by specifiying a txid.

Please backup your wallet.dat before running this command.

Arguments:
1. "txid"  (string, optional) The transaction id to keep.

Result:
{
 "total_transactions" : n,     (numeric) Transactions in wallet of VRSC
 "remaining_transactions" : n,   (numeric) Transactions in wallet after clean.
 "removed_transactions" : n,    (numeric) The number of transactions removed.
}

Examples:
> verus prunespentwallettransactions 
> verus prunespentwallettransactions "1075db55d416d3ca199f55b6084e2115b9345e16c5cf302fc80e9d5fbf5d48d"
> curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "prunespentwallettransactions", "params": [] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
> curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "prunespentwallettransactions", "params": ["1075db55d416d3ca199f55b6084e2115b9345e16c5cf302fc80e9d5fbf5d48d"] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
What information is returned by the `prunespentwallettransactions` command?

The `prunespentwallettransactions` command returns a JSON object with three properties:

* `total_transactions`: The total number of transactions in your wallet before pruning.
* `remaining_transactions`: The number of transactions remaining in your wallet after pruning.
* `removed_transactions`: The number of transactions removed from your wallet during pruning.

Can I use the `prunespentwallettransactions` command with a transaction ID to keep specific transactions?

Yes, you can use the `prunespentwallettransactions` command with a transaction ID to keep specific transactions. If you specify a transaction ID, the command will remove all spent transactions except for the one specified.

prunespentwallettransactions "txid"
